Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.05,0:00:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Day 2 earned me 3 cents.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.00,0:00:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}But the real cost was the three things I found.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.40,0:00:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I can't code.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.83,0:00:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}9 years in crypto.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.03,0:00:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I gave AI a thousand dollars to trade for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.76,0:00:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Day 2.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.88,0:00:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Around noon it placed its first real trade — bought one SOL contract at eighty-two seventy-six, sold it minutes later.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.08,0:00:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Balance went from one thousand to nine ninety-nine oh three.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.57,0:00:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Fees took 97 cents.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.18,0:00:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Sounds like nothing, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.11,0:00:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}But in those two minutes of watching, I noticed three things I'd been pretending not to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.47,0:00:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}One — the grid module.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.85,0:00:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Supposed to be live.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.62,0:00:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Still simulating orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.85,0:00:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I'd thought about whether this might break when I wrote the spec.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.40,0:00:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I decided probably not.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.36,0:00:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Two — seven of my backend servers bound to zero-zero-zero-zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.55,0:00:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Open to the entire internet.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.80,0:00:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}For a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.03,0:01:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Nothing bad had happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.00,0:01:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}But nothing bad yet isn't the same as nothing bad ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.53,0:01:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Three — a source file I'd pushed to public GitHub.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.47,0:01:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}My phone number, hardcoded.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.74,0:01:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}A three-cent profit exposed three pieces of work I'd been avoiding.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.61,0:01:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}In paper mode you never see these.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.33,0:01:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Real skin on the line is the only thing that shows them to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.86,0:01:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Day 3 tomorrow — I decided to give everything away for free.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.49,0:01:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Follow along.
